<div class="alert alert-info mb-4" role="alert">
    <h4 class="alert-heading"><span class="bi bi-info-circle"></span> MVVM Navigation Sample</h4>
    <p>
        This page demonstrates the MVVM navigation pattern in Blazor using the <code>IMvvmNavigationManager</code>. 
        Click "View Details" to explore the navigation flow:
    </p>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <h6><span class="bi bi-1-circle"></span> Users List (Current Page)</h6>
            <p class="small">
                Displays all users with action buttons. The <code>ViewUserDetailsCommand</code> uses 
                <code>NavigateTo&lt;UserViewModel&gt;(userId)</code> for type-safe navigation.
            </p>
            <h6><span class="bi bi-2-circle"></span> User Details Page</h6>
            <p class="small">
                Shows individual user information with route parameter binding. The <code>UserId</code> parameter 
                is automatically bound from the URL to the ViewModel.
            </p>
            <h6><span class="bi bi-3-circle"></span> User Posts Page</h6>
            <p class="small">
                Nested navigation displaying posts for a specific user. Demonstrates chained navigation 
                with breadcrumb navigation back to parent pages.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <h6><span class="bi bi-gear"></span> Features Demonstrated</h6>
            <ul class="small mb-0">
                <li><strong>Type-Safe Navigation:</strong> Navigate using ViewModels instead of string URLs</li>
                <li><strong>Route Parameters:</strong> Automatic binding of URL parameters to ViewModel properties</li>
                <li><strong>Command Pattern:</strong> Navigation triggered via <code>RelayCommand</code></li>
                <li><strong>Loading States:</strong> Async data loading with visual indicators</li>
                <li><strong>Breadcrumb Navigation:</strong> Multi-level navigation hierarchy</li>
                <li><strong>Service Integration:</strong> ViewModels consume services via dependency injection</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <hr />
    <p class="mb-0">
        <span class="bi bi-lightbulb"></span> <strong>Key Benefit:</strong> 
        MVVM navigation provides compile-time safety, better refactoring support, and cleaner separation 
        of concerns compared to traditional string-based navigation.
    </p>
</div>
